This article highlights the opinions of state legislators regarding the Affordable Care Act (ACA) and its potential repeal. Various state legislators express their support for the ACA and emphasize the benefits it has brought to their constituents. They mention improved access to affordable care, an end to lifetime limits on benefits, and the ability for young adults to stay on their parents' health care plan. These legislators argue that repealing the ACA would have negative consequences, such as eliminating coverage for pre-existing conditions, increasing costs for seniors, and adding to the national deficit. They stress the importance of maintaining and improving the current health care system rather than taking steps backward.